pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530107\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530107\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 05, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104mvs1665702903514.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mvs1665702903514.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mvs1665702903514.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"mvs1665702903514\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Remotely Validating XML Streams\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You can use XML streams to pass data to another component for validation. This process is known as remote validation. The benefit of remote validation is that validation logic can be centralized and located in dedicated validation components.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"mvs1665702903514__context_w6553ab1b5b1_w6554ab1b5_w6555ab1\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"mvs1665702903514__topic_d38339e1_d38340e1_d38341e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mvs1665702903514__p_d38342e1_d38343e1_d38344e1\">To remotely validate an XML stream:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step\" id=\"mvs1665702903514__li_d19406e1_d19407e1_d19408e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Send the data as an XML stream to the validation component. The XML stream must include the <code class=\"ph codeph\">id</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">crc</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">status</code> and <code class=\"ph codeph\">valerr</code> attributes for all entity elements in the XML stream, and include the <code class=\"ph codeph\">valerr</code> attribute for all field elements.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"mvs1665702903514__li_d19409e1_d19410e1_d19411e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Load the data from the XML stream into the validation component, and reconnect the data to component and database data, using <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"thr1665702690548.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/thr1665702690548.html\" title=\"Reconnect data loaded from a disconnected record set (XML, JSON, or Struct) with the occurrences in a database or component.\">retrieve/reconnect</a>.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"mvs1665702903514__li_d19412e1_d19413e1_d19414e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Validate the data. If necessary, modify the error triggers to set values for the <code class=\"ph codeph\">errormsg</code> property of <code class=\"ph codeph\">$occproperties</code> and <code class=\"ph codeph\">$fieldproperties</code>. Exit the error trigger with a negative value, for example <code class=\"ph codeph\">return -1</code>.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"mvs1665702903514__li_d19415e1_d19416e1_d19417e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Send the data back to the initial component as an XML stream using the <code class=\"ph codeph\">id</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">crc</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">status</code>, and <code class=\"ph codeph\">valerr</code> attributes. Values for <code class=\"ph codeph\">errormsg</code> are placed in the <code class=\"ph codeph\">valerr</code> attribute by the <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ebq1665702566280.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ebq1665702566280.html\" title=\"Places component data in an XML stream.\">xmlsave</a> statement.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"mvs1665702903514__li_d19418e1_d19419e1_d19420e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Load the data from the XML stream into the initial component. Each <code class=\"ph codeph\">valerr</code> attribute encountered by <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vuu1665702574732.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vuu1665702574732.html\" title=\"Load data from an XML stream into occurrences drawn on the component.\">xmlload</a> fires an occurrence-level or field-level error trigger, with <code class=\"ph codeph\">$error</code> is 0161.\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sua1665702566764.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Attributes in Uniface XML Streams</a><p>Uniface uses attributes in XML streams to store data processing information and to define custom attributes.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vna1665702566998.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface XML Stream Processing</a><p>Uniface uses the xmlsave and xmlload ProcScript statements to transfer and convert data (including validation and modification state) between Uniface component and XML streams. Attributes determine the state of data in an XML stream. These are defined in the DTD for the XML stream.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530107\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530107\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Remotely Validating XML Streams Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 05, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Remotely Validating XML Streams You can use XML streams to pass data to another component for validation. This process is known as remote validation. The benefit of remote validation is that validation logic can be centralized and located in dedicated validation components. To remotely validate an XML stream: Send the data as an XML stream to the validation component. The XML stream must include the id , crc , status and valerr attributes for all entity elements in the XML stream, and include the valerr attribute for all field elements. Load the data from the XML stream into the validation component, and reconnect the data to component and database data, using retrieve/reconnect . Validate the data. If necessary, modify the error triggers to set values for the errormsg property of $occproperties and $fieldproperties . Exit the error trigger with a negative value, for example return -1 . Send the data back to the initial component as an XML stream using the id , crc , status , and valerr attributes. Values for errormsg are placed in the valerr attribute by the xmlsave statement. Load the data from the XML stream into the initial component. Each valerr attribute encountered by xmlload fires an occurrence-level or field-level error trigger, with $error is 0161. Related Links Attributes in Uniface XML Streams Uniface uses attributes in XML streams to store data processing information and to define custom attributes. Uniface XML Stream Processing Uniface uses the xmlsave and xmlload ProcScript statements to transfer and convert data (including validation and modification state) between Uniface component and XML streams. Attributes determine the state of data in an XML stream. These are defined in the DTD for the XML stream. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}